description._content: Catalog #: 15_000006 Title: Charles M. Daniels Collection Photo Aircraft/Subject: Bell P-39Q Airacobra Daniels Album Name: 71st Tactical Reconnaisance Group Reunion, 10/1990 Houston, TX Notes From Album: Bell P-39Q Airacobra of the 82nd Tactical Reconnaissance, New Guinea. Additional Information: SOC (Struck Off Charge) May 21, 1945 at Tadji, Papua New Guinea. Recovered 1972-73. Displayed at Moorabin Air Base, Australia from 1982 to 1988. Restored to static display for the Museum of Flight, Santa Monica, Ca. 1991-1994. Bought by the Fighter Collection, Duxford, England. Restored to flying condition by Fighter Rebuilders, Chino, CA. First flight as N-139DP on June 14, 2004. Re-registered as G-CEJU on May 21, 2007. Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
